An '''information minister''' (also called '''minister of information''') is a position in the [[government]]s of some countries responsible for dealing with [[information]] matters.

==Information ministries==
'''Minister of Information''' may refer to:
*{{flag|Afghanistan}}: Minister of Information and Culture [http://www.moic.gov.af/pages/biography.php]
*{{flag|Australia}}:  [[Minister for Broadband, Communications and the Digital Economy (Australia)]] [http://www.dbcde.gov.au/]
*{{flag|Bahrain}}: Minister of Information [http://www.info.gov.bh/en/]
*{{flag|Bangladesh}}: Minister of Information [http://www.moi.gov.bd/]
*{{flag|Cambodia}}: Minister of Information [http://www.information.gov.kh/]
*{{flag|Eritrea}}: Minister of Information [http://www.shabait.com/staging/index.html]
*{{flag|Egypt}}: Ministry of Information and Communication
*{{flag|Ethiopia}}: Minister of Information [http://www.moinfo.gov.et/]
*{{flag|Fiji}}: Minister of Information [http://www.info.gov.fj/]
*{{flag|Nazi Germany}}: [[Ministry of Public Enlightenment and Propaganda|Minister of Public Enlightenment and Propaganda]] - (A Historical position in Nazi Germany)
*{{flag|India}}: [[Ministry of Information and Broadcasting (India)|Ministry of Information and Broadcasting]]
*{{flag|Indonesia}}: [[United Indonesia Cabinet|Minister of Information and Communication]]
*{{flag|Iraq}}: [[List of Iraqi Information Ministers|Information Minister]] - (A historical position during the presidency of [[Saddam Hussein]])
*{{flag|Jamaica}}: Minister of Information, Culture, Youth & Sports [http://www.jis.gov.jm/information/index.asp]
*{{flag|Jordan}} :Ministry of Information and Communication Technology
*{{flag|Kenya}}: Minister of Information and Communications [http://www.information.go.ke/]
